{
    "unitNumber": 6,
    "text": {
        "title": "Adverbs",
        "sections": [
            {
                "title": "Forming Adverbs with -mente",
                "paragraphs": [
                    {
                        "id": 6.01,
                        "content": "English adverbs are usually formed by adding ‘-ly’ to an adjective (e.g. ‘thinly’, ‘cleverly’). Italian adverbs are usually just as easy to form: **-mente** is added to the feminine singular form of the adjective:",
                        "table": {
                            "rows": [
                                [
                                    "**lenta + -mente**",
                                    "**lentamente**",
                                    "slowly"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**rapida + -mente**",
                                    "**rapidamente**",
                                    "quickly"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**semplice + -mente**",
                                    "**semplicemente**",
                                    "simply"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**frequente + -mente**",
                                    "**frequentemente **",
                                    "frequently"
                                ]
                            ]
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "content": "When the adjective ends in **-le** or **-re** preceded by a vowel, the final **e** is dropped before adding **-mente**:",
                        "table": {
                            "rows": [
                                [
                                    "**gentile + -mente**",
                                    "**gentilmente**",
                                    "kindly, politely"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**utile + -mente**",
                                    "**utilmente**",
                                    "usefully"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**maggiore + -mente**",
                                    "**maggiormente**",
                                    "mainly"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**regolare + -mente**",
                                    "**regolarmente**",
                                    "regularly"
                                ]
                            ]
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "table": {
                            "rows": [
                                [
                                    "**Il tempo cambia rapidamente.**",
                                    "The weather changes quickly."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**La nonna cammina lentamente.**",
                                    "Granny walks slowly."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Enrico risponde sempre gentilmente.**",
                                    "Enrico always answers politely."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Faccio i compiti regolarmente.**",
                                    "I do my homework regularly."
                                ]
                            ]
                        }
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Other Adverbs",
                "paragraphs": [
                    {
                        "id": 6.02,
                        "content": "In Italian there are also many adverbs which do not end in -mente. * Note that with non ... ancora and non ... mai, non is always placed before the verb and ancora/mai after it. Here are some:",
                        "table": {
                            "rows": [
                                [
                                    "**abbastanza**",
                                    "enough/fairly/rather/quite"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**ancora**",
                                    "still"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**bene**",
                                    "well"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**davanti**",
                                    "at the front/in front"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**dentro**",
                                    "in(side)"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**dietro**",
                                    "at the back/behind"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**dopo**",
                                    "later/afterwards"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**forte**",
                                    "loudly/hard"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**fuori**",
                                    "out/outside"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**già**",
                                    "already"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**lontano**",
                                    "far (away)"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**male**",
                                    "badly"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**non ... ancora**",
                                    "not yet"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**non ... mai**",
                                    "never"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**piano**",
                                    "slowly/quietly"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**più**",
                                    "more"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**piuttosto**",
                                    "rather"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**presto**",
                                    "soon/early"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**prima**",
                                    "earlier/beforehand/first"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**quasi**",
                                    "almost"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**sempre**",
                                    "always"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**sopra**",
                                    "above/upstairs"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**sotto**",
                                    "below/downstairs"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**spesso**",
                                    "often"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**subito**",
                                    "immediately/right away"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**tardi**",
                                    "late"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**vicino**",
                                    "near(by)"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**volentieri**",
                                    "willingly/gladly"
                                ]
                            ]
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "table": {
                            "rows": [
                                [
                                    "**Questo film è abbastanza bello.**",
                                    "This film is rather good."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Partiamo tardi: dopo le 11.**",
                                    "We’re leaving late: after 11."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Andiamo spesso in discoteca.**",
                                    "We often go to the disco."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Vengo subito!**",
                                    "I’m coming (immediately)!"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Parto presto.**",
                                    "I’m leaving early/soon."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Parliamo piano perché Carla dorme.**",
                                    "We’re talking quietly because Carla’s asleep."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Può parlare piano, per favore? Non sono italiano.**",
                                    "Could you speak slowly, please? I’m not Italian."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Abita vicino, Signora?**",
                                    "Do you live nearby (Madam)?"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Vai lontano?**",
                                    "Are you going far?"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Piove forte.**",
                                    "It’s raining hard."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Puoi parlare più forte?**",
                                    "Can you speak louder/more loudly?"
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**Mangiamo fuori.**",
                                    "We’re eating out [e.g. in a restaurant]/outside [i.e. in the open]."
                                ],
                                [
                                    "**È ancora estate.**",
                                    "It’s still summer."
                                ],
